**Step 4o: Value-gap hunter (NEW 2026-05-04 -- see bead `flywheel-1rmp`, Joshua directive "what else can we add value to that we're not thinking of currently").**

Run the canonical value-gap probe. This is not a normal health probe. It asks
which high-leverage measurement the flywheel is not asking for yet, rotates
through ten dimensions, and files at most one low-priority bead per real tick.
It must never dispatch directly from the finding.

```bash
/Users/josh/Developer/flywheel/.flywheel/scripts/value-gap-probe.sh --json
```

Initial dimensions:
1. Cross-repo failure-mode harvester
