- `value_gap_finding`
- `bead_filed_id`
- `value_gap`

Guardrails:
- Lower priority than FLEET_REPAIR, DISPATCH_BEAD, VALIDATE, and callback reap.
- File a bead, do not dispatch it directly.
- Cap one value-gap bead per tick.
- Dry-run mode must not mutate bead state or the value-gap ledger.

**Dimension-1 measurement: cross-repo-failure-mode-harvester** (bead
`flywheel-1rmp.2`). Read-only aggregator over memory feedback files'
`trauma_class:` field + per-repo `INCIDENTS.md` `## ` headers. Surfaces
trauma classes appearing in N+ sources (default N=2) BEFORE the third
rediscovery, so the orchestrator can decide on doctrine promotion before
a class becomes load-bearing in three places.

```bash
.flywheel/scripts/cross-repo-failure-mode-harvester.sh --json
```

Self-logs to `~/.local/state/flywheel/cross-repo-failure-mode-harvester.jsonl`
on every run. Per Step 4o anti-pattern guardrail: SURFACES candidates
only — does NOT auto-file beads or auto-dispatch. The orchestrator
consumes the JSONL ledger or invokes the script live to decide whether
a recurring class should escalate (memory promotion to INCIDENTS,
INCIDENTS promotion to AGENTS L-rule, or fleet-wide bead).

**Dimension-3 measurement: customer-facing-observability** (bead
`flywheel-1rmp.4`). Read-only per-client aggregator over each client
repo's `.beads/issues.jsonl` (bead state aggregates, ready/stale/
closed-last-7d counts), `.flywheel/last_closeout_receipt.json` (last
shipped close age), `.flywheel/dispatch-log.jsonl` (recent activity),
and `INCIDENTS.md` (open trauma surface count). Default client roster
is `alpsinsurance terratitle` (Blackfoot Telecom runs on external
substrate, so no flywheel-managed repo to probe).

```bash
.flywheel/scripts/customer-facing-observability.sh --json
```

Self-logs to `~/.local/state/flywheel/customer-facing-observability.jsonl`
on every run. Per Step 4o anti-pattern guardrail: SURFACES per-client
risk_signals and value_signals only — does NOT auto-dispatch client
work. The orchestrator (or Joshua) decides when a customer-visible
risk signal warrants action.

**Dimension-9 measurement: adversarial-orchestrator-self-audit** (bead
`flywheel-1rmp.10` shipped, `flywheel-myfak` wired, `flywheel-myfak.1`
executed). Read-only adversarial sweep of orchestrator behavior:
punt_phrase_count + mission_drift_count + unaddressed_skill_routes +
recent_closed_beads_without_evidence.

```bash
.flywheel/scripts/adversarial-orch-self-audit-probe.sh --json
```

Self-logs to `~/.local/state/flywheel/adversarial-orch-self-audit-probe-runs.jsonl`
on every run. Per Step 4o anti-pattern guardrail: SURFACES findings only —
does NOT auto-file beads, does NOT auto-dispatch, does NOT mutate state.
Read-only by design (br/ntm/gh/git/agent-mail untouched per probe header
contract).

