- `inbox_messages`

If unread messages are present, include an `## Inbox pre-tick (<identity>)`
block in the tick prompt with message ids, senders, subjects, and excerpts.
The script MUST NOT auto-reply, mark messages read, or acknowledge messages.
The orchestrator decides each reply manually via Agent Mail `reply_message`;
when it replies, it also sends a paired `ntm send` notification to the sender's
session/pane per L61. Token files are existence-checked only and token values
must never be printed.

If any repo reports `LIMPING`, `MISSING`, `STALE`, `BLOCKED`, invalid JSON, or
the roster cannot be read, append SOFT violation
`orch_fleet_onboard_probe_degraded`, preserve per-repo rows, and continue.
Stamp/sync/upgrade modes remain Joshua-approved mutation paths and must not be
triggered by tick.

