### Step 8d: Storage headroom watcher

At tick close, after dispatch/refill decisions and before returning control to
the loop driver, run the storage headroom watcher with the auto threshold:

```bash
/Users/josh/Developer/flywheel/.flywheel/scripts/storage-headroom-watcher.sh \
  --trigger tick \
  --auto \
  --json
```

The watcher defaults to dry-run behavior. `--auto` switches to `--apply` only
when `disk_free_gb < 50.0`, uses a 55GB buffer, and stops pruning once it
reaches 60GB or exhausts the safe category list. During dry-run ticks, omit
`--auto`.

### Step 8e: Tick-hook firing verifier

Before a tick-close primitive can claim `tick_hook_wired=yes`, L116 requires it
to be registered in the real process manifest:

```bash
jq -e '.schema_version == "tick-driver-manifest.v1" and (.primitives | length > 0)' \
  /Users/josh/Developer/flywheel/.flywheel/scripts/tick-driver-manifest.json
```

The recurring process is `/Users/josh/.local/bin/flywheel-tick-driver`, loaded
by `/Users/josh/Library/LaunchAgents/com.flywheel.tick.plist`. `tick.md` is the
decision function; the driver is the process that makes registered primitives
fire without a human/agent rereading this document.

After all tick-close hooks above, run the verifier so tick receipts distinguish
"no events" from "hook never fired":

```bash
/Users/josh/Developer/flywheel/.flywheel/scripts/tick-hook-firing-verifier.sh \
  --apply \
  --json
```

If any primitive is `invisibly_broken`, keep the tick open long enough to file
or update the corresponding repair bead; do not report `tick_hook_wired=yes`
from script presence alone.

### Step 8f: Peer orchestrator drift probe

At tick close, after all other tick-close hooks, run the peer-orch drift probe
to detect mission-alignment drift across all fleet sessions:

```bash
DRIFT_JSON="$(
  /Users/josh/Developer/flywheel/.flywheel/scripts/peer-orch-drift-probe.sh \
    --json 2>/dev/null
)" || DRIFT_EXIT=$?
DRIFT_EXIT="${DRIFT_EXIT:-0}"
```

Parse the result:
- If exit code 0: all sessions <20% drift — record
  `peer_orch_drift_status=ok` and `peer_orch_drift_max_pct` in tick receipt.
- If exit code 1 (20-40%): record `peer_orch_drift_status=warn`. Do NOT halt
  the tick; the probe writes its own alert to
  `~/.local/state/flywheel/peer-orch-drift-alerts.jsonl`.
- If exit code 2 (>=40%): record `peer_orch_drift_status=critical`. Flag for
  escalation in SOFT: `peer_orch_drift_critical`.

Tick receipt fields from `$DRIFT_JSON`:
- `peer_orch_drift_aligned_count` = `.aligned_session_count`
- `peer_orch_drift_total_count` = `.total_session_count`
- `peer_orch_drift_max_pct` = `.max_drift_pct`
- `peer_orch_drift_dashboard_line` = `.dashboard_line`

If `--dry-run`, pass `--dry-run` to the probe so no alerts are written.

SOFT violation: `peer_orch_drift_probe_skipped` if Step 8f is absent from the
tick receipt.

Note: agent-mail delivery of ALIGNMENT WARNING messages is handled by the probe
itself (via `~/.local/bin/agent-mail` if available, else JSONL-only). The tick
need not re-send.

## Dispatch Callback Contract

Every dispatch from this tick MUST include callback instructions in the
dispatch file. Workers cannot close the feedback loop if they don't know
how to report back. The dispatch boilerplate must include:

```markdown
## Callback (REQUIRED)
When done, send your results back to the orchestrator:
1. Write results to /tmp/<output_file>.md
2. Look up the callback_pane from ~/.local/state/flywheel/session-topology.jsonl for the target session:
   `CALLBACK_PANE=$(jq -sr --arg s "<session>" 'map(select(.session == $s)) | sort_by(.effective_at) | last | .callback_pane // .orchestrator_pane' ~/.local/state/flywheel/session-topology.jsonl)`
3. Send callback: ntm send <session> --pane="$CALLBACK_PANE" "Callback: task_id=<TASK_ID> status=done output=/tmp/<output_file>.md evidence_redacted=<yes|no|n/a>"
If you hit a blocker: ntm send <session> --pane="$CALLBACK_PANE" "Callback: task_id=<TASK_ID> status=blocked reason=<one-line> evidence_redacted=<yes|no|n/a>"
```

## L61 Pairing (NEW 2026-05-01 — see flywheel-2yf)

Every fleet-mail send (`mcp__mcp-agent-mail__send_message`) MUST be paired with
an `ntm send` to the same recipient's session+pane containing the `message_id`
and `project_key`, so the receiver fetches immediately. Async-only fleet-mail
without ntm-poke is effectively dropped because orchestrators don't auto-poll
inbox between explicit triggers.

Without this, dispatched work is fire-and-forget — the orchestrator has to
poll for results instead of being notified. This is the information flow
that closes the Meadows feedback loop.

## Output

```
TICK: <project> @ <tier> — <UTC ISO>

  Autoloop: <N> receipts since last tick, last status=<status>
  Fuckup-log: <N> unprocessed events
  Awareness: mission=<read|missing>, goal=<locked|drift>, state_age=<hours|null>
  Inbox: <N> handled, <N> dispatches, <N> beads
  Fuckups: <N> beaded, <N> no-bead, <N> skipped
  Skillos routed: <N> decisions surfaced
  Panes: <idle-count> idle, <working-count> working
  Fleet: <ready>/<opted_in> ready, flags: [<list>]
  Bead graph: top blockers [<ids>], dispatched=<id|null>
  L61: <cross-session N> messages, dual-channel=<pct|null>
  VC: status=<ok|degraded|unavailable>, alerts=<N>, digest=<summary|null>
  Mission lock: status=<fresh|stale-warn|stale-error|unlocked|missing>, age_hours=<N|null>, id=<id|null>
  Leverage: score=<N|null>/1000, binding=<accounts|machines|tokens|none|unknown|null>, warnings=<N>
  Gaps: total=<N|null>, new=<N|null>, top_class=<class|null>, warnings=<N>
  Decision: <DECISION>
  Action: <what was done, or "none">
  Dispatches: <N> sent, <N> callbacks pending
  Refill: <sent bead-id|deferred reason|not applicable>
  Violations: <list or "none">

  Next tick: <ISO timestamp>
  Receipt: ~/.local/state/flywheel-loop/last_tick_<project>.json
```

## Constraints

- **Phase A.1 scope.** 8 tick steps plus refill invariant: autoloop receipts,
  fuckup-log, pane states, fleet self-diagnosis, decision, receipt, callback
  reap, idle-worker refill, schedule next.
- **SOFT mode only.** All violations are logged, none halt. Graduation to
  WARN/HALT comes in Phase B when the L56 ladder query is wired up.
- **No worker ticks.** `/flywheel:worker-tick` is a separate Phase B command.
- **Doctrine tier special behavior.** When tier=doctrine, the tick focuses on
  fleet health, cross-repo synthesis, and doctrine custodianship.
- **No report-then-die.** When `tier=doctrine` and `idle_workers > 0`,
  `IDLE_CLEAN` is a SOFT violation: `orch_idle_with_capacity`. The tick MUST
  find work through `DOCTRINE_HUNT` or explicitly document why every hunt check
  found no dispatchable work.
- **Idempotent.** Running tick twice in quick succession produces the same
  receipt (the second tick sees "last tick was <1min ago" and emits IDLE_CLEAN
  only if the doctrine idle-worker guard is satisfied).
- **Callback-first dispatch.** Every dispatch includes `ntm send` callback
  instructions. Fire-and-forget dispatch is a SOFT violation:
  `orch_dispatched_without_callback`.
- **Awareness step required before dispatch decisions.** Step 1a must precede
  any decision in Step 5. SOFT violation: `orch_skipped_awareness`.
- **Inbox check graceful degrade.** Step 2b is conditional on `flywheel-1e8`
  and `flywheel-bpd`. Until those land, log
  `inbox_skipped_reason=no_identity_token` and proceed.
- **Fuckup-bead-or-no-reason enforced.** Step 2c MUST decide each unprocessed
  fuckup. SOFT violation: `orch_skipped_fuckup_decision`.
- **Skillos routed decisions are read-only from flywheel.** Step 2c may read
  `~/.local/state/flywheel/skillos-routed.jsonl` only through
  `~/Developer/flywheel/.flywheel/scripts/skillos-routed-tail.sh`; routed-file
  writes are skillos-owned.
- **PageRank cadence.** Step 4g runs every 12 ticks OR on `DOCTRINE_HUNT` with
  idle workers. Skipping when conditions are met is a SOFT violation:
  `orch_skipped_pagerank`.
- **L61 pairing enforced.** Step 4h audits last K cross-session messages.
  Counter-example = SOFT violation `orch_l61_violation_ntm_only` or
  `orch_l61_violation_mail_only`.
- **Fleet-coherence consumer.** Step 4i is fail-open. Default mode is read-only:
  it may write receipt fields, but must not run `br create`, finalize
  `no_bead_reason`, or dispatch `FLEET_REPAIR`. Action mode requires explicit
  `FLYWHEEL_FLEET_COHERENCE_STEP4I_MODE=actions`,
  `FLYWHEEL_FLEET_COHERENCE_ACTION_APPLY=1`, and a non-`--dry-run` tick.
- **Vibe Cockpit probe graceful degrade.** Step 4i.1 is fail-open. If the canonical
  Vibe Cockpit CLI is missing or degraded, append
  `orch_vc_observability_degraded`, preserve the warning in the receipt, and
  continue.
- **Mission-lock age probe is read-only.** Step 4j may warn on stale, unlocked,
  missing, or lock-log-mismatched MISSION.md state, but it must not relock or
  write mission files during tick.
- **Leverage-ceiling probe graceful degrade.** Step 4l is fail-open. If the
  canonical leverage probe is missing, degraded, or cannot observe an input
  stock, append `orch_leverage_ceiling_observability_degraded`, preserve the
  warning in the receipt, and continue.
- **Gap-hunt probe graceful degrade.** Step 4n is fail-open. If the canonical
  gap-hunt probe is missing, degraded, or cannot observe a gap class, append
  `orch_gap_hunt_probe_degraded`, preserve the warning in the receipt, and
  continue.
- **Value-gap hunter lower priority.** Step 4o is a paradigm-tier scan for
  missing measurements, not a health gate. It may file at most one P2/P3 bead
  per real tick and never dispatches directly. Dry-run ticks must keep it
  read-only.
- **Agent Mail FD doctor graceful degrade.** Step 4r is fail-open. FD pressure,
  missing launchd child process, or schema drift append
  `orch_agent_mail_fd_doctor_degraded`, preserve probe checks, and continue.
- **Mobile-eats receipt bridge graceful degrade.** Step 4s is fail-open and
  read-only. Missing flagship receipts append
  `orch_mobile_eats_receipt_bridge_degraded`, preserve bridge warnings, and
  continue.
- **Codex watchtower doctor-only in tick.** Step 4t never runs the GitHub ingest
  mutation path. It reads the latest watchtower summary, verifies the pinned
  Codex tracker, and cross-references frozen-pane-detector v2 strikes. Missing
  ledgers, invalid JSON, stale pin, or detector schema drift append
  `orch_codex_watchtower_degraded` and preserve `codex_warnings`.
- **Daily Jeff ingest doctor-only in tick.** Step 4u never runs the ingest
  mutation path. Missing dependencies append `orch_daily_jeff_ingest_degraded`
  and scheduled ingest owns snapshots, mirrors, and bead filing.
- **Fleet onboarding doctor dry-run only.** Step 4v may inspect fleet member
  health but must not stamp, sync, or upgrade repos from tick. Non-healthy rows
  append `orch_fleet_onboard_probe_degraded`, preserve per-repo rows, and
  continue.
- **Inbox check is surface-only.** Step 4w may read RubyCreek unread messages
  and place excerpts in the prompt. It must not reply, mark read, ack, or touch
  peer-orch identities. Replies require orchestrator decision plus paired L61
  `ntm send` notification.
- **Jeff philosophy is doctor-only in tick.** Step 4x reads the current pattern
  catalog and latest daily snapshot path. It never runs deep-mine or
  daily-snapshot mutation from tick; absent patterns append
  `orch_jeff_philosophy_degraded`.

